  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "They smote also the tents of cattle,.... The people that dwelt in tents for the sake of the pasturage of their cattle; the Scenite Arabs, so called from dwelling in tents: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and carried away sheep; which those Arabs were feeding in Palestine, and which this great army brought with them for their support: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and camels in abundance; which is another circumstance proving them to be Arabs, who abounded with camels: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and returned to Jerusalem; with their spoil, and with great joy. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and returned to Jerusalem; with their spoil, and with great joy. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
